# Article Writing Rules (Gapta)

Applies when `src/content/articles/**` exists. Until then, use **gapta-article-writer** skill and [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) as the target contract.

## File structure

`src/content/articles/{slug}/index.mdx` — slug: Latin `kebab-case` (e.g. `vybir-stabilizatora`).

```
src/content/articles/{slug}/
├── index.mdx
├── imgs/
│   └── cover.avif
└── components/     # optional, when React is in the project
```

## Draft vs publish

Before setting draft/publish in frontmatter, **ask the user**. Field names (`draft`, `isDraft`, etc.) must match the real Astro collection schema.

## Frontmatter (template — align with code)

```yaml
---
draft: true
title: ""           # Ukrainian, SEO; length per project schema
description: ""     # Meta description
cover: "./imgs/cover.avif"
coverAlt: ""
category: obladnannya   # embroidery-related category id
author: leonid-m        # or authors: [] if schema uses array
publishedTime: "2026-04-03T00:00:00.000Z"
---
```

### Category examples (embroidery)

`obladnannya`, `nythky-polotno`, `digitizing`, `prohramne`, `oglyady`, `porady` — adjust to real category IDs in the repo.

### Authors

Default author id: `leonid-m` unless others exist in `src/content/authors/`.

## MDX body

- **Language:** Ukrainian for prose headings and paragraphs
- **Headings:** `##` / `###` in body; no extra `#` h1 if the layout already sets the title
- **React:** import from `./components/…` with `client:load` / `client:visible` when React is available
- Short paragraphs, lists, fenced code with language tags

## SEO

- Keywords natural in title, description, headings
- Internal links to other **Gapta** articles when they exist
- Alt text in Ukrainian for images

## Images

- Store under `./imgs/`; prefer AVIF or WebP
- `cover` path relative to `index.mdx`
